rComments: He is a great lecturer and he really cares that every student understand the material. Before every test, he did a study session that lasted until the last student left. He gives feedback extremely quickly (in less than a week). This is great, especially considering that he has over 600 students! I'd definitely take another course offered by him.

There's a decent amount of online homework , which can be tedious but is pretty easy and boosts your grade. There's extra credit every week to make up for when you forget an assignment or skip lecture. Clegg does review sessions before every test and if you go you're pretty much guaranteed to do well on the test.

Clegg is a funny man, very energetic and obviously passionate about biology. His test are nothing like his slides, notes, etc. They are mostly critical thinking problems which makes them extremely difficult and confusing. Some would say this is a blow off class, I beg to differ.

The class can be a little difficult but the professor goes above and beyond to make sure each student receives the help that he/she needs to pass. Obvious that he is very passionate and knowledgable about the subject. Takes student feedback into consideration. Phenomenal professor.
great. helps with whatever you need. will always be available. even if the class is hard, you'll be okay as long as you put some effort in.
It is easy class. There's a lot of chances for extra credit. I got 75 for my first exam and 80 for my final, but still managed to get an A.
Easier than AP bio, and the final has a generous curve. My raw score was a solid B, and with the curve it went up to a solid A

I loved Ben! He truly knows the subject he's teaching and is super eager to make sure we understand everything. Toughness is average, and it's not hard to get a good grade if you put in the effort. His office hours are great, and you can tell he's wants us to learn, which is great. He cares more about our learning than just points.
Great teacher. Loads of extra credit,  easy online homework. Tests are fair if you study.

Ben is great!!!! Very generous with extra credit.  Tests are reasonable, but be sure to study.  Online homework is pretty easy, lots of answers can be found on Quizlet and other webpages.  Highly recommend him.  Wish I could have another class just like this one.

Dr. Clegg was such a great professor. He makes the class pretty easy. Do the extra credit, it adds up to around 75 points. I blew off the last test and final and still got an A. Don't forget to do the learning catalytics and homework though. They definitely boost your grade. Overall great, and interesting class.

Sooo nice! Tests aren't particularly hard if you review the prelectures and lecture powerpoints. Extra credit galore. And very enthusiastic about what he teaches! I'm sad that I'll likely never have him again, and I actually wish I had gone to office hours to get to know him better. Only bad part is grading can be harsh on experimental design stuff

He is a good professor. Enthusiastic and clearly enjoys the subject he teaches. If you need any help, office hours are very useful and he hold review sessions before all of the tests. Tests are fairly easy, and he usually drops a question or two. Due to the nearly 80 extra credit1000 total points, it is pretty easy to get a good grade as well.
Very great professor! My fellows all admire him a lot. Clarity and efficiency!

Clegg literally jumps at the chance to help his students. He is a good teacher because of his great passion for biology and he really cares about his students whether he knows their names or not. He is a really good guy. On the negative side, he can occasionally ramble and his lectures can be a tad confusing.

Although Dr. Clegg's lectures can seem confusing at times, he is a great teacher who is willing to invest all of his time into his students. He is very passionate about Biology and wants to ensure that everyone understands the material taught. If you do the Learning Goals before each Hour Exam, you'll do well on his tests. Lots of extra credit too.
Good!
class is super easy just the test are kind of hard so study and go over notes.

He was very into teaching and would really spend time with the students during office hours explaining a certain concept. If you really show up during lecture and finish off all the work, there's no reason not to get good grades.

Great class to take freshman year. It provides a different perspective on biology and Ben is a great professor! However, if you really want to pass, I suggest going to office hours and studying outside of lecture as some of the material has a lot of content to cover.
